<div class="nass margin-top-10"> <p><span id="p1" class="anchor"></span>This classification includes material related to the recording of Hadith and biographies of reporters.<a href="#p1" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p2"></span>- TXT: Text<a href="#p2" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p3"></span>The original texts of all Hadith books are in Arabic, but this classification is for translated works.<a href="#p3" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p4"></span>- USU: Usul<a href="#p4" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p5"></span>The terminology and explanation of Mustalah writings (Science of Hadith) come into this category.<a href="#p5" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p6"></span>- WRI: Writings<a href="#p6" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p7"></span>All other general works on Islam that deal specifically with aspects of the Hadith and Sunnah are classified in this category.<a href="#p7" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p>
<p><span class="anchor" id="p8"></span><span class="c5">ملاحظة:</span> - طبعت أسماء الكتب بالحرف الأسود، أمّا أسماء البحوث المنشورة في المجلات فهي بالحروف المائلة.<a href="#p8" class="btn_tag btn btn-sm"><span class="text-gray fa fa-copy"></span></a></p> </div>